# Lugarithm — AI integration secrets
# Copy this file to ".env" (same folder) and paste your real key(s). ".env" is gitignored.
#
# While Unity is open, edits to .env are detected and synced automatically within
# about one second. The manual menu and pre-build sync remain available. This writes
# Assets/Resources/ai_config.json for local prototyping; do not ship a production
# client with a private key embedded in it. Use a backend relay for production.

# Google Gemini API keys — power Co-Pilot hints, Coding Mentor, Heritage Oracle,
# Vibe Coding, and the Living Story engine. Get keys at https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
#
# Up to five free-plan keys are supported. At runtime the AI falls back across them
# (and down the model ladder) when a key hits its quota — fill as many as you have.
# Plain GEMINI_API_KEY also works as an alias for slot 1.
GEMINI_API_KEY_1=
GEMINI_API_KEY_2=
GEMINI_API_KEY_3=
GEMINI_API_KEY_4=
GEMINI_API_KEY_5=

# Optional per-key model fallback order (comma-separated), walked top-to-bottom for
# each key before advancing to the next key. Leave commented to use the built-in
# default (the five IDs below). Override to change the rotation:
# GEMINI_MODEL_LADDER=gemini-3.5-flash,gemini-3.1-flash-lite,gemini-2.5-flash,gemini-2.5-flash-lite,gemini-3.0-flash
